registry.title: example
registry.note:
The 'example' media type is used for examples. Any subtype following the media type syntax may be used in those examples. No subtype can be registered with IANA. For more information see.
Note: The occurrence of an 'example' media type as a media type outside of examples, e.g. in a Content-Type header, is an error and should be reported to the implementor. specifies that Content Types, Content Subtypes, Character Sets, Access Types, and conversion values for MIME mail will be assigned and listed by the IANA.
